Key Match Events: Angola's goalkeeper Neblu was sent off after 17 minutes for handling the ball outside his penalty area.
Namibia's Lubeni Haukongo received a red card for a second bookable offense just before halftime.
Gelson Dala scored two goals in a remarkable four-minute span just before halftime.
Post-Match Reflections: Neblu's emotional dismay was palpable as he received a red card.
The goals showcased Angola's resilience and adaptability in the face of challenging circumstances.
